<div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1670485569663" class="gf_row gf_row-fluid gf_row-no-padding gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1670485569663" data-extraclass="" data-row-gap="0px" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1655318047095" data-id="1655318047095"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1670485569653" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1670485569653" data-layout-lg="9+3" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="9+3" data-layout-sm="9+3" data-layout-xs="12+12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-9 gf_col-md-9 gf_col-sm-9 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1656408976790" data-id="1656408976790"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1670485569629" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1670485569629" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1658814063462" data-id="1658814063462"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1670485569701" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1670485569701" style="min-height: auto; display: block;" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1656316047890" data-id="1656316047890" style="min-height: 1px; display: block; flex-direction: unset; justify-content: unset;"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1670485569581" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1670485569581" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1656408976790" data-id="1656408976790"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569813" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670485569813"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Treadmills for Beginners vs Treadmills for Professionals</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680592366856" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680592366856" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Whether you're a beginner or a professional runner, different treadmills are designed to suit your needs. I’ve discussed the main differences below:</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569817" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670485569817"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Adjustability&nbsp;</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569816" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670485569816" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Different treadmill adjustments may include the running deck speed, incline settings, and safety rail placement. Beginner treadmills tend to offer a smaller range or sit at the slower end of these adjustment options. Professional runners need a much larger and higher range of running speeds or incline settings to provide a <a href="https://www.verywellfit.com/quick-and-effective-treadmill-workouts-3866052" class="" target="_blank">suitable workout stimulus</a> as they progress.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680592420397" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1680592420397"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Monitor Functions</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673764626941" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673764626941" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Beginner treadmills tend to offer less monitor functionality which may include Bluetooth compatibility, preset workout programs, integrated speakers, and custom LCD display screens.</p><p>These are all features that improve your running experience but are not needed for a good workout.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685382387806" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1685382387806"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Construction</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685382409674" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1685382409674" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The construction materials used in professional treadmills tend to be of higher quality, which increases the max user capacity and durability. However, this makes them heavier and therefore less portable compared to beginner treadmills.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673770422035" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1673770422035" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/43beb490-7755-428c-b1c5-60f155ff8f4b/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/WBCM-Treadmill-Performing.jpg" alt="WBCM Performing Treadmill" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="WBCM Performing Treadmill" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680592618207" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1680592618207"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What to Look for in the Best Treadmills for Beginners</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1672895061465" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1672895061465" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Here are the main factors to look out for when purchasing the best treadmill for home use. Make sure to consider each factor and decide what you want to use the treadmill for first.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1672895064923" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1672895064923"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">Adjustability</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685377499425" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1685377499425" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Different treadmill adjustment options can change your workout experience, comfort, and available workout options. Consider the number of speed and incline options the treadmill offers and compare it to your workout goals and current ability level. If you enjoy incline running, make sure the treadmill offers incline settings.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701391918832" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701391918832" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701391918795" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701391918795" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701391918857" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1701391918857"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-4" id="c-1686566621695" data-id="1686566621695"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701391918774" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1701391918774" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-right-lg gf-elm-right-md gf-elm-right-sm gf-elm-right-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d583efb1-a2f6-4d53-8a26-d6ddafaa60fd/7350738.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="512" height="512" data-width="50%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="512" natural-height="512"></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701391918781" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701391918781"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="">Beginner treadmills offer a simple yet effective way to provide an at-home running workout. They offer fewer functionality and design features compared to their more expensive counterparts that are better suited for professional runners. Differences in overground vs treadmill running may take awhile to get used to at first.</div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701391918806" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701391918806" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564763470" data-id="1686564763470"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701391918779" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1701391918779" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" target="_blank"><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/fc0a1a19-2e31-4fa8-a43b-9c408a123923/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Oleksiy.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="531" height="533" data-width="20%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="531" natural-height="533"></a></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564765807" data-id="1686564765807"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701391918811" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701391918811"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><b><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" class="" target="_blank">Oleksiy Torokhtiy</a></b></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701391918824" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701391918824"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: 700;">Olympic Weightlifting&nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: 700; color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Champion</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679507965936" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1679507965936"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Monitor Functionality</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679507967430" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679507967430" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Different monitor functions can change your whole running experience depending on what you’re looking for. Things to look out for include screen workout metrics, Bluetooth compatibility, and the placement of the quick-press buttons.</p><p>Most of these aren’t that important for you to achieve a decent workout, but can help you to enjoy running more. They may also matter more as you increase your ability level.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1677242690479" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1677242690479" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/321422c2-3a43-4806-9525-7d2a16c70d33/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Using-Treadmill-in-the-Gym.jpg" alt="WBCM Training on Treadmill" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="WBCM Training on Treadmill" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679507986292" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1679507986292"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">Portability</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679507988029" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679507988029" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>If you’re looking for a treadmill that’s easy to move around, consider the frame weight, frame dimensions, and whether transportation wheels are included. Check that the treadmill folds away, with a hydraulic lifting system helping to do this safely.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670506766447" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670506766447"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Comfort&nbsp;</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569819" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670485569819" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>As a beginner runner, comfort can be important when you're starting out your running journey. <a href="https://www.runnersworld.com/uk/health/injury/a773762/4-causes-of-knee-pain-and-how-to-fix-them/" class="" target="_blank">Joint pain</a> can be a common issue when you're still getting used to the movement. Look for a treadmill that contains shock absorption software under the running deck.</p><p>Added safety features such as safety rails and emergency stop buttons help to improve user comfort and ensure peace of mind when you’re still learning.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680592756728" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1680592756728"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Value for Money</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680592761019" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680592761019" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Most beginner treadmills offer excellent value for money. If you’re on a budget, consider the price of different treadmills to what they offer. Factors such as adjustability, monitor functions, and portability should all be taken into account when deciding the best choice for you.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679516684454" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1679516684454" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/c93935e0-5f50-4aa9-9abb-a5a6515c95d6/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Athlet-Using-Treadmill.jpg" alt="WBCM Treadmill Using" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="WBCM Treadmill Using" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680592862073" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1680592862073"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">How to Use a Treadmill Correctly</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680592908018" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680592908018" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Follow the tips below on <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HxsFneJFM2c" class="" target="_blank">how to use your treadmill</a> correctly and look after it with care:</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680592902657" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1680592902657"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Warmup and Cool Down Correctly</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1685377718646" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1685377718646" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Performing a suitable <a href="https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/24748668.2019.1566846" class="" target="_blank">warm-up and cool-down</a> before and after running is important, especially as a beginner.</p><p>Begin with some dynamic stretches and a brisk walk before increasing your intensity. After your workout, slowly decrease the intensity to lower your heart rate and reduce the chance of injury.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680593003169" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1680593003169"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Maintain Correct Running Posture</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680593004978" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680593004978" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Keep your chest up, your head facing forward, and maintain a neutral spine when running. Look to keep your hips and legs correctly aligned and stride out whilst keeping your arms relaxed and arms bent at 90 degrees. This <a href="https://www.kheljournal.com/archives/2015/vol1issue4/PartC/34.1-429.pdf" class="" target="_blank">correct running posture</a> limits the chances of injury and helps with running performance.</p><p>Use the safety rails provided for a quick rest if you can’t maintain the correct posture.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781715573" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1675781715573" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/a4b55ea4-698d-4db5-86f5-eb883847a184/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/WBCM-Training-With-Treadmill.jpg" alt="Running in The Gym on Treadmill" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="Running in The Gym on Treadmill" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680593031312" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1680593031312"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Perform Regular Maintenance</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680593034287" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680593034287" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Make sure to follow the manufacturer's maintenance instructions to keep your treadmill running as intended. Clean it regularly, lubricate the necessary joints, and check the belt tread. Tighten any loose joints and check the electric cable if applicable.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680593064913" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1680593064913"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Keep Hydrated</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680593067276" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680593067276" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Drink water or a sports drink solution small and often during your running workout to keep <a href="https://core.ac.uk/download/pdf/41306999.pdf" class="" target="_blank">hydrated</a>. Use the water bottle holder if provided</p><p>Check the Safety Features</p><p>Familiarize yourself with the included safety features such as the emergency stop button and safety rails. Use them correctly when you need and make sure you know how they operate.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787440275" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787440275"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">FAQ</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787464047" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787464047"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Is a 20-Minute Treadmill Workout Effective?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787891143" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787891143" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><div>Yes, a 20-minute treadmill workout is effective to achieve several workout goals when performed regularly. Make sure to tailor the intensity according to your individual needs.&nbsp;</div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787889767" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787889767"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Are Cheap Treadmills Worth It?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680593611864" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680593611864" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p></p>Cheap treadmills offer excellent value for money compared to their more expensive counterparts. They offer slightly less monitor functionality and adjustable options but are great for beginner users who want a treadmill without spending a fortune.<div><div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680593609639" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1680593609639"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Is It Okay to Use a Treadmill Every Day?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679508113086" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679508113086" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p></p>Treadmills can be used every day with little issues if you manage your intensity and recovery correctly. However, it’s always good to have a rest day or two incorporated into your workout routine to allow your body and mind to recover.<div><div></div><div></div><div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1675788016791" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1675788016791" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context": "https://schema.org","@type": "FAQPage","mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question","name": "Is a 20-Minute Treadmill Workout Effective?","acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer","text": "Yes, a 20-minute treadmill workout is effective to achieve several workout goals when performed regularly. Make sure to tailor the intensity according to your individual needs."}},{"@type": "Question","name": "Are Cheap Treadmills Worth It?","acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer","text": "Cheap treadmills offer excellent value for money compared to their more expensive counterparts. They offer slightly less monitor functionality and adjustable options but are great for beginner users who want a treadmill without spending a fortune."}},{"@type": "Question","name": "Is It Okay to Use a Treadmill Every Day?","acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer","text": "Treadmills can be used every day with little issues if you manage your intensity and recovery correctly. However, it’s always good to have a rest day or two incorporated into your workout routine to allow your body and mind to recover."}}]}</script></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787968593" clas